COVID-19 Background¶

Since December 2019, COVID-19 disease (commonly labelled as the coronavirus or covid) is an infectous disease caused by SARS-CoV-2 virus. The coronavirus can be spread from person to person (WHO, 2023). The virus can spread from an infected persons mouth or nose in small liquid particles when they cough, sneeze, speak, sing or breathe. As of January 15, 2023 the total cases of covid 19 is 671,323,775 with 6,730,373 deaths and 642,409,943 recovered within the total cases (worldometer, 2020). It has infected over 229 countries with it being in its 4th major variant (Omicron). It can be diagnosed through viral with two main types of viral tests being nucleic acid amplification tests (NAATs) and antigen tests (CDC, 2022). Since Dec. 11, 2020, there have been international releases of the covid vaccine which has saved many lives from the pandemic (as aforementioned 642,409,943 recovery).

Introduction & Purpose of Project¶

Our group aims to understand better of covid-19 and it's affect on the United States in the different states. We'll look at the datasets that looks at the states records of covid cases and vaccinations. For the first half explores and analyzes the datasets independently and draw interpretations from it. The second half will merges both datasets to see any correlation and make conclusions.

The datasets we'll be looking into are will be "all-states-history.csv" from https://covidtracking.com/data on the states records of covid cases. The second dataset we'll look at is ""us_state_vaccinations.csv" from "https://www.nature.com/articles/s41562-021-01122-8" which looks at vaccination records from covid-19 cases.

COVID-19 Vaccination Background¶

Fortunately we have been able to combat covid-19 with vaccinations which has saved millions of lives. Accordign to the CDC, there are 4 approved vaccines in the US. These are:

1. Pfizer-BioNTech COVID-19 vaccine
2. Moderna COVID-19 vaccine
3. Johnson & Johnson's Janssen COVID-19 vaccine
4. Novavax COVID-19 vaccine

(CDC, 2022)

As of 2022 more than 900 million doses have been released across all 50 states of the United States. The initial release of the covid-19 vaccines as well as it's protocols to mantain infection was made with backlash and negligence from the public the US. Causes of backlash stem from socieconomic to political factors however most of the public was able to catch on the severity of the pandemic's transmissive.

Endogeneity¶

Our scatterplots are definitely not concretely evidental for a final conclusion of the correlation between the variables that are in the dataset to draw a clear understanding of the effects that covid-19 has on the states within the US and how the US has been combating with covid-19 vaccines. This can be drawn from the histogram where we used boolen method which in return showed missing data. Another issue was when we were cleaning the data of null values and had to use backwards filling method in addition to the command "fillna" which in certain situations can help a dataset operate better however with ours this could've led to dubplicate numbers filling in for the variable columns that have missing entries.

Conclusion¶

Overall, we had a lot of data findings that were insightful and reflects the true correlations that have been searched upon on this research of covid-19's impact on the US. We were able to draw the states with the largest number of report both in vaccination distribution and covid-19 cases. There clear relations that states with higher cases of covid-19 leds to an increase in all areas of variables. One notable consistency to draw in as an outlier are the states Flordia and California. Whereas Florida shows that its has a consistent linear regression in all it's variable from covid-19 reports to vaccinations, California shows an exponential growth in it's variables.

The graphs conducted from this project also solidifies or at the least draws the connection of the US's initial response to covid-19 where the state was met with protests and backlash on the government's attempt to facilitate and mandate the pandemic hence the initial higher increase that all states experience at the start until a slower more stable increase later on.

Hopefully readers have found this research imformative and learn better on the operations used to build a simple yet insightful project using python jupyter notebook.
